The paper deals with completeness theorems in logic and their connections to game semantics and ludics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also discusses the use of induction and countermodels, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with propositional logic (cs.PL) and linear logic (cs.CC), which are both relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper touches on game theory (cs.GT) in its discussion of game semantics.
